== Git Tools

By now, you've learned most of the day-to-day commands and workflows that you need to manage a Git repository.
You've accomplished the basic tasks of tracking and committing files, and you've harnessed the power of the staging area, lightweight topic branching, and merging.

Now you explore a number of very powerful things that Git can do that you may not necessarily use on a day-to-day basis but you may need at some point.

